        "design.comparison": "planned",
        "design.tuning": "verified",
        "validation.rules": "planned",
        "validation.build-diff": "planned"
      },
      "limitations": [
        "SwiftUI content is described by synthesizing nodes from accessibility elements, so it is only observable while an accessibility runtime is active. A dormant capture reports ios.capture.content-not-observable and the Screen Graph refuses it as identity evidence.",
        "Synthesized SwiftUI element nodes carry no bounds, z_index, clipped, or visual facts; only the UIKit view hierarchy contributes geometry."
      ]
    },
    "android": {
      "implementation_status": "in-progress",
      "initial_adapter": "view-viewgroup",
      "capabilities": {
        "runtime.snapshot": "verified",
        "runtime.events": "verified",
        "runtime.connection": "verified",
        "automation.actions": "verified",
        "automation.safety": "verified",
        "exploration.graph": "verified",
        "state-identity.normalization": "verified",
        "design.comparison": "planned",
        "design.tuning": "verified",
        "validation.rules": "planned",
        "validation.build-diff": "planned"
      },
      "limitations": [
        "Compose content is described by its semantics tree, not its composition tree, so a node exists only where a composable declares semantics. Nodes that are measured but not placed (LazyList prefetch) are excluded, because they carry no layout truth.",
        "Compose semantics expose no z_index, color, or font, and the only route to text layout is an action an observation-only capture must not invoke. Compose host nodes report android.capture.compose-visual-unavailable, and the screenshot remains the visual truth for those subtrees.",
        "Automatic View event observation is not implemented; the Demo App reports transient events explicitly through the bounded recorder."
      ]
    }
  },
